org.apache.paimon.flink.action.cdc.format.maxwell

Class MaxwellRecordParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.paimon.flink.action.cdc.format.RecordParser
      • org.apache.paimon.flink.action.cdc.format.maxwell.MaxwellRecordParser
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, org.apache.flink.api.common.functions.FlatMapFunction<CdcSourceRecord,RichCdcMultiplexRecord>, org.apache.flink.api.common.functions.Function

    public class MaxwellRecordParser
extends RecordParser
    The MaxwellRecordParser class extends the abstract RecordParser and is designed to parse records from Maxwell's JSON change data capture (CDC) format. Maxwell is a CDC solution for MySQL databases that captures row-level changes to database tables and outputs them in JSON format. This parser extracts relevant information from the Maxwell-JSON format and converts it into a list of RichCdcMultiplexRecord objects.

    The class supports various database operations such as INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE, and creates corresponding RichCdcMultiplexRecord objects to represent these changes.

    Validation is performed to ensure that the JSON records contain all necessary fields, and the class also supports schema extraction for the Kafka topic.
